Transform data types

train <- train %>% 
  select(FLOOR, BUILDINGID, SPACEID, RELATIVEPOSITION, USERID, PHONEID) %>% 
  apply(2, as.factor) %>% 
  cbind(
    select(train, LONGITUDE, LATITUDE, TIMESTAMP, 1:520)
  )
train$TIMESTAMP <- as.POSIXct(train$TIMESTAMP, origin = '1970-01-01', tz = 'GMT')
valid <- valid %>% 
  select(FLOOR, BUILDINGID, SPACEID, RELATIVEPOSITION, USERID, PHONEID) %>% 
  apply(2, as.factor) %>% 
  cbind(
    select(valid, LONGITUDE, LATITUDE, TIMESTAMP, 1:520)
  )
valid$TIMESTAMP <- as.POSIXct(valid$TIMESTAMP, origin = '1970-01-01', tz = 'GMT')

Maximum strength of each WAP

maxStr_train <- train %>% 
  select(10:529) %>% 
  summarise_all(max) %>% 
  t() %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  rownames_to_column()
head(maxStr_train)
maxStr_valid <- valid %>% 
  select(10:529) %>% 
  summarise_all(max) %>% 
  t() %>% 
  as.data.frame() %>% 
  rownames_to_column()
head(maxStr_valid)

We filter out WAP’s with maximum strength = -110

max110_tr <-
  maxStr_train %>% 
  filter(V1 == -110)
max110_val <-
  maxStr_valid %>% 
  filter(V1 == -110)
inner_join(max110_tr, max110_val, by = "rowname") %>% 
  nrow()
[1] 0

The 55 WAP’s without reception (all values = -110) in train are totally different from the 153 WAP’s without reception in valid. Let’s exclude them all.
